The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 Taj Leisure Hotels has unveiled ?Taj Holidays? across various exotic destinations. Taj will also launch the ?Summer Holiday Offer? in India, Sri Lanka, Maldives, Mauritius, Seychelles and Dubai from May 1 to September 30 and till October 15 at Taj Leisure Hotels in Goa and Kerala. Guests can also opt for advance booking offers, which are valid only for stays between May 1 and June 15, 2005. Under this, guests booking and paying up 30 days before the check-in date can get the fourth night free (room only) on a three nights stay at any of the Taj Leisure Hotels in Goa and the third night free (room only) on a two nights stay at all other Taj Leisure Hotels, except in Ooty and Coonoor.

 Canbank Mutual Fund has declared a dividend of 10 per cent under Canbalance and 4 per cent under Cancigo, the record date being April 15. Prudential ICICI Mutual Fund has declared April 5 as the record date for dividend distribution under its Discovery Fund.

 AMP Sanmar Life Insurance has launched Divya Shree ? an endowment plan with compound bonus. Divya Shree offers add-on riders, including term assurance benefit and convenient premium options, both single and regular. 




